                            <comment id="12789290" author="rob.stryker" created="Fri, 12 Jul 2013 05:49:02 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;From our test, some other raw output:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;execute command:  /home/rob/apps/jboss/zipped/wildfly-8.0.0.Alpha2/bin/jboss-cli.sh  --controller=192.168.1.102:9999 --connect command=:shutdown, which fails: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   org.jboss.as.cli.CliInitializationException: Failed to connect to the controller&lt;br/&gt;
           at org.jboss.as.cli.impl.CliLauncher.initCommandContext(CliLauncher.java:291)&lt;br/&gt;
           at org.jboss.as.cli.impl.CliLauncher.main(CliLauncher.java:257)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12789301" author="dlofthouse" created="Fri, 12 Jul 2013 06:23:28 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-1664&quot; title=&quot;bin]$ ./jboss-cli.sh -c --controller=localhost:9999 - Results in Connection Timed Out&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WFLY-1664&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WFLY-1664&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is already under discussion to provide better handling of the different protocols available for use with the CLI not that a HTTP upgrade is also possible.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The tail end of the discussion is that if port 9999 is selected then we will default to pure Remoting and this situation will not happen.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
